                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/1341</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey (<persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                            type="from">
                            <hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi>
                        </persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-27T17:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 27, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 31, 2.45 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1520. My 1486, January 17, 11 a. m.<note n="1" xml:id="d1215fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> Captain Blakeley of the <hi rend="italic">Des Moines</hi>
                    telegraphs from Naples that he will be unable to proceed from Piraeus to Beirut
                    as no ships whatever are allowed to enter Syrian blockade. Only available route
                    open for Red Cross party is via Constantinople.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgenthau</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
